main event: A radar operator on a US Coast Guard cutter observed a large, high-speed target on radar that appeared to rise rapidly out of the water and take off at tremendous speed in a level flight over the Atlantic Ocean.
interesting points: The object appeared as a large target on the radar screen, indicating it was a sizeable object.
The object traveled at a high speed and rose rapidly out of the water, suggesting it was not a conventional aircraft or vessel.
The object's behavior, including its rapid ascent and high-speed level flight, was described as unusual and potentially new or unusual.
Other radar-based sightings of unidentified objects were reported in the Project Blue Book documents.
The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes.
sighted object: a large, high-speed target on radar
witnesses: radar operator on a US Coast Guard cutter
